{{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Harper's Bible Dictionary | title_orig = | translator = | image = Harper's Bible Dictionary.jpg<!--prefer 1st edition--> | author = [[Paul J. Achtemier]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = Bible studies | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | publisher = [[Harper and Row]] | pub_date = 1985 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]]) | pages = | isbn = 0-06-069863-2 | dewey= 220.3 19 | congress= BS440 .H237 1985 | oclc = 12262764 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Harper's Bible Dictionary''''' is a scholarly reference book of the [[Bible]], containing the texts of the Old Testament, the Apocrypha, and the New Testament. It is written by 180 members of the [[Society of Biblical Literature]], edited by [[Paul J. Achtemier]], and containing 3500 articles and 400 photographs.
It has a [[Library of Congress Classification|LCC]] of BS 440.H237.<ref>[http://library.furman.edu/resources/subject/relig/religref.htm Religion Resources]</ref>
