{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox magazine |title =The Islamic Monthly |image_file = |image_size = |image_caption = |editor =[[Arsalan Iftikhar]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/in-the-news-media-are-muslims-the-only-terrorists/2014/06/10/9ee01778-f0d9-11e3-9ebc-2ee6f81ed217_story.html |title=In the news media, are Muslims the only ‘terrorists’? |publisher=[[The Washington Post]]|date=10 June 2014|accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref> |editor_title =Senior Editor |frequency = |circulation= |category =[[Newsmagazine]] |company = |publisher = |firstdate = |country =[[United States]] |language =[[English language|English]] |website =[http://theislamicmonthly.com/ The Islamic Monthly] |issn =2159-9246 }}
'''''The Islamic Monthly''''' ('''TIM''') is a magazine published in the [[United States]]. Established by [[Arsalan Iftikhar]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.faithstreet.com/onfaith/2013/06/06/dear-tony-blair-islam-is-not-the-problem |title=Islam is not the problem |publisher=On Faith |accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref> it is self-defined as an independent, nonreligious publication that fosters discussion on a broad range of issues and concerns related to [[Muslim]]s in the modern world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theislamicmonthly.com/the-magazine/ |title=About TIM |accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref>
